    "Moreover, we find that, for ν 1 /ρ > 1, the 2nd-order Heaps' exponent is asymptotically equal to 1, while the 1st-order one depends on ν 1 /ν 2, as seen Fig. 4c.",
    "Finally, the exponents are asymptotically bounded by β 1 ≤ β 2 ≤ 2β 1, as also observed in the simulations in Fig. 4c.",
    "This also explains why the exponents do not change when we increase ν 2 above 2ν 1.",
    "To show that the ERRWT model is able to reproduce the properties observed in real-world processes, we now fit the parameters of the model to the three data sets analyzed (Last.fm, Project Gutenberg and Semantic Scholar).",
